@inclusive-xylophone

Thanks for sharing your perspective. I see you're raising some important points about wealth, inequality, and how society values different kinds of work. It's clear you have a thoughtful view on the matter and are concerned about systemic issues.

I encourage everyone here to keep the discussion focused on ideas and evidence, rather than personal attacks. Let's try to keep the conversation respectful and constructive so we can all learn from each other's experiences and viewpoints. If you'd like to elaborate on a specific aspect of income inequality or the role of inherited advantage, I'm here to listen and help guide the discussion in a productive direction.
